Sentencas: The Cr deposition reaction is investigated between the La0.9Sr0.1 MnO3 (LSM) cathode and Fe-Cr alloy interconnect at 750 degrees C for solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: The investigation of interaction between La0.9Sr0.1 MnO3 cathode and metallic interconnect for solid oxide fuel cell at reduced temperature

Sentencas: The poison effect on cathode is observed by a group of orthogonal experiments at the presence of Fe-Cr alloy involving with air flow and current passages.
Titulo: The investigation of interaction between La0.9Sr0.1 MnO3 cathode and metallic interconnect for solid oxide fuel cell at reduced temperature

Sentencas: After the current polarization, the cathode layer has been delaminated from the electrolyte (YSZ), and the Cr deposition reaction is accelerated with adding air partial pressure.
Titulo: The investigation of interaction between La0.9Sr0.1 MnO3 cathode and metallic interconnect for solid oxide fuel cell at reduced temperature

Sentencas: When the LSM cathode has undergone Cr poison for 3000 min with current passage of 400 mA cm(-2) and air flow of 100 mL(-1) two rapid increase stages of polarization potential E-cathode are found, which can be reasonably explained by Cr deposition resulting in cathode delaminated from the electrolyte layer.
Titulo: The investigation of interaction between La0.9Sr0.1 MnO3 cathode and metallic interconnect for solid oxide fuel cell at reduced temperature

Sentencas: Furthermore, the Cr deposition ring and two kinds of Cr-contain agglomerates are observed in the interface of LSM/YSZ, which indicates that the formation of Cr2O3 and (Cr,Mn)(3)O-4 oxides, respectively.
Titulo: The investigation of interaction between La0.9Sr0.1 MnO3 cathode and metallic interconnect for solid oxide fuel cell at reduced temperature

Sentencas: This suggests that the deposition of Cr species would preferentially occur at the three phase boundary region and the trend to agglomeration in long time operation.
Titulo: The investigation of interaction between La0.9Sr0.1 MnO3 cathode and metallic interconnect for solid oxide fuel cell at reduced temperature
